(11, '68) To define what columns should be displayed in an SQL SELECT statement:', 'a. Use FROM to name the source table(s) and list the columns to be shown after SELECT.', 'b. Use USING to name the source table(s) and list the columns to be shown after SELECT.', 'c. Use SELECT to name the source table(s) and list the columns to be shown after USING.', 'd. Use USING to name the source table(s) and list the columns to be shown after WHERE.', 'a', 'Not Avavilable'),
